    "name": "Residential Links Under the Weather",
    "datePublished": "2019.08",
    "description": "Weather is a leading threat to the stability of our vital infrastructure. Last-mile Internet is no exception. Yet, unlike other vital infrastructure, weather&rsquo;s effect on last-mile Internet outages is not well understood. This work is the first attempt to quantify the effect of weather on residential outages. ",
